Subject: Argentina Rules of Conduct for Marketers

Among the several notices received from the ENARGAS last week were two items 
of immediate interest.  We received a notice of the Public Hearing which is 
scheduled for March 7th.  This hearing though is being described as a public 
hearing on the general issue of "Open Access" to distribution services 
including the resulting rates for such services rather than a public hearing 
on Ecogas' refusal to provide interruptible distribution services as 
requested by Renault.  The LDCs and Marketers were specifically invited as 
well as a number of government agencies and enduser associations but Renault 
was not directly invited.  "Industrial users with a lawful interest in the 
issue" were invited and this appears to be the invitation intended for 
Renault.  I am not sure of the rational for this change but according to the 
regulatory team we were not expecting this switch. 

The second item of interest is the request for comments regarding the 
establishment of "Rules of Conduct for Marketer's Activity".   Mike's summary 
of the request as well as a translation of the request is set forth below.

Let me know if you need any more information.

Brent

