Subject: Argentina Rules of Conduct for Marketers

The natural gas regulatory body of Argentina "ENARGAS" has initiated a study 
of "Activities of Traders" in the natural gas sector. They are soliciting 
comments of industry participants on the following specific issues and any 
others deemed pertinent to be used in an analysis performed by the ENARGAS to 
establish future rules and regulations governing marketers.

1 Effective competition between distcos and marketers
2 Information provided by distcos and marketers to users
3 Tools used by marketers to capture users in compliance with independence, 
transparency and equity criteria
4 Types of services offered by marketers and contractual schemes used
5 Criteria for supply curtailments
6 Compliance to gas dispatch rules (ENARGAS Resolution No. 716/98), 
adequately following imbalances and nominations in the transportation 
systems   

Worst Case: In that Enron is the only commercially active marketer in 
Argentina, this study can be viewed as predatory and potentially restrictive 
to our future growth potential.
 
Best Case: As an industry we could collectively develop beneficial rule of 
conduct that will facilitate market growth, real competition, and better 
market protection from dominant sector players.

Guillermo Canovas will lead the effort to develop our formal response. Please 
assist by providing any supporting comments, suggestions, or information that 
may be deemed useful in developing and our position.  We have to respond by 
February 9th. 

ENARGAS 
Letter of Solicitation




MFG


